Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to upper position and preheat oven to 400 degrees. Bring a #medium pot{} of salted water to a boil. Halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1}. Halve @heirloom grape tomatoes{4%oz} and @lemon{1}. Crush @black peppercorns{1%tbsp} in #bag{} with a #mallet{} or #pan{}. Mix @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} and a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tbsp} in a #small bowl{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once water is boiling, add half the @gemelli pasta{3%oz} to #pot{} (use the rest as you like). Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Scoop out and reserve 1/4 cup pasta cooking water, then drain. Meanwhile, pat @rib-eye steak{12%oz} dry with a #paper towel{}. Season all over with salt and as much of the crushed peppercorns as you like.

Whisk together 1 tsp shallot, 2 tsp lemon juice, and @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #medium bowl{}. Season with salt and pepper. Set aside. Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add half the remaining shallot and cook, tossing, until softened, about ~{3%minutes}. Add @flour{1%tbsp}. Stir until pasty, about ~{1%minute}. Slowly whisk in @milk{6.75%oz} until combined.

Bring milk mixture to a boil and let bubble until thickened, about ~{1%minute}. Remove from heat, then stir in @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup} and @truffle zest{0.07%oz}. Stir in gemelli, followed by enough reserved pasta water to give sauce a loose consistency. Season with salt and pepper. Lightly oil two #ramekins{}, then divide gemelli and its sauce between each. Sprinkle panko over gemelli. Bake in oven until lightly browned and bubbly, about ~{10%minutes}.

Wash out pan used for mac ’n’ cheese. Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{4-7%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and set aside. Set pan aside off heat for a few minutes to cool slightly, then return to stove over medium-low heat. Add remaining shallot to same pan and cook, tossing, until just softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Pour in 1/3 cup water and @beef stock concentrate{1}.

Scrape up any browned bits from bottom of pan, then simmer until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add @mixed greens{2%oz} and tomatoes to #bowl{} with dressing and toss to coat. Season with salt and pepper. Slice steak, then divide between plates. Drizzle with sauce from pan. Serve with mac ’n’ cheese and salad.